tr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/5212d822baaa77b1b817b22eca7af0d2"><gtr:id>5212d822baaa77b1b817b22eca7af0d2</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Rice, A.J.</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2012-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:isbn>978-0-7546-7356-9</gtr:isbn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/A93073CE-D7B5-4871-98B0-36C02014E6EF"><gtr:id>A93073CE-D7B5-4871-98B0-36C02014E6EF</gtr:id><gtr:title>Introduction: imagining transatlantic slavery and abolition</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Patterns of Prejudice</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/a2a1f75d4bc0c952fd9cd8c3bc024a31"><gtr:id>a2a1f75d4bc0c952fd9cd8c3bc024a31</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Oldfield J</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2007-01-01</gtr:date></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/E6359A4C-3019-4E08-B057-EC668E493319"><gtr:id>E6359A4C-3019-4E08-B057-EC668E493319</gtr:id><gtr:title>Tracing slavery and abolition's routes and viewing inside the invisible: The monumental landscape and the African Atlantic</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Atlantic Studies</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/83774c4d1fc79e93c6c0c0c856978ce1"><gtr:id>83774c4d1fc79e93c6c0c0c856978ce1</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Rice A</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2011-01-01</gtr:date></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/1F7CC2F3-4C9F-48BD-A387-B5801E96617B"><gtr:id>1F7CC2F3-4C9F-48BD-A387-B5801E96617B</gtr:id><gtr:title>Revealing Histories, Dialogising Collections: Museums and Galleries in North West England Commemorating the Abolition of the Slave Trade</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Slavery &amp; Abolition</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/83774c4d1fc79e93c6c0c0c856978ce1"><gtr:id>83774c4d1fc79e93c6c0c0c856978ce1</gtr:id>